00:23:42,413 --> 00:23:45,635
We were called out in some comments for not getting the colors right or for it to having

442
00:23:45,655 --> 00:23:46,676
a slightly odd look.

443
00:23:47,056 --> 00:23:50,539
The truth was it was an unfinished asset that had slipped out into the wild like sometimes

444
00:23:50,579 --> 00:23:51,460
happens unfortunately.

445
00:23:52,961 --> 00:23:55,863
But we were also called out for not realizing what the character was.

446
00:23:56,967 --> 00:23:59,669
Some people saw a lizard character, that was the actual intent.

447
00:24:00,810 --> 00:24:02,191
Others saw some kind of moving plant.

448
00:24:02,551 --> 00:24:06,474
They were discussing what they remember seeing in the original game.

449
00:24:07,155 --> 00:24:10,117
The real truth was more complicated.

450
00:24:10,637 --> 00:24:15,300
It was some kind of cyborg lizard with a laser eye, with a molten frill, with bionic parts.

451
00:24:15,981 --> 00:24:19,984
You know, a pretty complex set of characteristics to illustrate in such low fidelity.

452
00:24:20,604 --> 00:24:23,786
Something that's actually a little hard to deconstruct for even a current artist.

453
00:24:25,665 --> 00:24:29,728
You know, it was funny, it was a little silly, but it was an illuminating moment for us.

454
00:24:30,529 --> 00:24:36,112
We established that personal interpretation is a potential challenge for anyone remastering

455
00:24:36,132 --> 00:24:37,553
games like Crash or that vintage.

456
00:24:39,454 --> 00:24:43,937
You know, luckily there was great rejoicing when this one asset seemed to be adequate

457
00:24:44,058 --> 00:24:44,498
at release.

458
00:24:44,518 --> 00:24:49,521
You know, I think posts like this are more kind of in jest about the...

459
00:24:50,565 --> 00:24:54,547
amount of scrutiny that almost every aspect of a game being remastered goes through.

460
00:24:55,107 --> 00:24:59,429
But still the point being, if people care about what you're doing and if you're remastering

461
00:24:59,469 --> 00:25:04,891
something, probably people care about it, you've got to understand that you're going

